President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama send their warm wishes to those celebrating Kwanzaa. They acknowledge the week-long celebration of African American heritage and culture, which is based on the seven principles of Kwanzaa: unity, self-determination, collective work and responsibility, cooperative economics, purpose, creativity, and faith. The Obamas celebrate Kwanzaa as a time for reflection and gratitude for the past year while also recognizing the challenges faced by many Americans. They emphasize the importance of unity and overcoming challenges together. The Obamas send their well wishes and blessings for a happy and healthy new year to all families celebrating Kwanzaa.